LAST-MODIFIED:20260410T023404Z
UID:10011604-1776369600-1776374100@www.unexpectedproductions.org
SUMMARY:Pratidhwani and Unexpected Productions Present Improv-Asana
DESCRIPTION:What happens when South Asian artistry meets Seattle’s longest-running improv tradition? Nobody knows. That’s the whole point. \n\n\n\n\nOn Thursday\, April 16th\, 8:00 PM\, Pratidhwani and Unexpected Productions are sharing a stage for the first and only time\, and you’re not just watching. You’re part of it. \nFor more than 20 years\, Pratidhwani has championed South Asian performing artists and built community through the power of live performance. Since 1983\, Unexpected Productions has been turning audience suggestions into full-blown theatrical moments. Together\, we’re bringing two distinct creative worlds into the same room to see what sparks\, and\, given the talent involved\, there’s going to be a lot of laughter. \nAnasuya (Ana) Basu\, Anise Rau\, Gauri Shringarpure\, Ronak Sharma\, Siddhant Sharma\, and Sumant Gupta \nDirected by Siddhant Sharma \nYour suggestions\, your joy\, and your ideas are the fuel. These artists will take whatever you throw at them and turn it into something that will suprise everyone… and make you laugh out loud while doing it!
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/pratidhwani-and-unexpected-productions-present-improv-asana/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike Place Market\, Seattle\, WA\, 98101\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Improvasana-2080x1080-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
