SUMMARY:Clown 200: Reinforcing Your Clown Foundation with Mick Holsbeke
DESCRIPTION:Deepen your clown craft through presence\, rhythm\, status\, and physical comedy—embracing failure to build confidence\, independence\, and play\n\n\n\nIn the Clown 200 class series\, students will deepen their understanding of the foundations of theatrical clowning. Participants will engage in exercises focused on presence\, rhythm\, tension\, emotional endurance\, character development\, status play\, and physical humor. By embracing failure and mistakes\, students build confidence to take new comic risks\, grow in their comedic abilities\, and gently approach independence in harnessing the elusive state of Clown. \nClass Details\nDates: Six (6) Thursday classes \nTime: 5:30 – 7:00 PM \nLocation: The Clown Garage at Improv School Eastside Issaquah \n1315 NW Mall Street\, Suite 4 Issaquah\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill) \nMaximum students: 12 \nAges: 18 plus \nPrerequisite: None
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/clown-200-reinforcing-your-clown-foundation-with-mick-holsbeke/
LOCATION:Clown Garage at the Improv School Issaquah\, 1315 NW Mall Street\, Suite 4\, Issaquah\, WA\, 98027
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Clown-200.png
END:VEVENT
